@startuml
title Section 2.1 - Use Case Diagram - RSE Conference Website

left to right direction

actor Visitor as V

rectangle "RSE Conference Website" as SYS {
  usecase "Browse About/Home" as UC_About
  usecase "View Important Dates" as UC_Dates
  usecase "View Schedule" as UC_Schedule
  usecase "View Venue & Directions" as UC_Venue
  usecase "Browse Organizers & Steering Committee" as UC_Org
  usecase "Browse Previous Editions" as UC_Past
  usecase "Contact Organizers via Email" as UC_Email
  usecase "Apply (when application-page enabled)" as UC_Apply
  usecase "Register" as UC_Register
  usecase "Open Travel Plan Document" as UC_TravelDoc
}

V --> UC_About
V --> UC_Dates
V --> UC_Schedule
V --> UC_Venue
V --> UC_Org
V --> UC_Past
V --> UC_Email
V --> UC_Apply
V --> UC_Register
V --> UC_TravelDoc

' External systems explicitly referenced in code
actor "Google Forms" as GF
actor "Google Docs" as GD
actor "Email Client" as MAIL
actor "Google Maps" as GM
actor "Past Event Sites" as PES

' Mappings to external services (links/embeds present in code)
UC_Register ..> GF : redirects to forms.gle
UC_TravelDoc ..> GD : opens docs.google.com
UC_Email ..> MAIL : mailto: organizer email
UC_Venue ..> GM : iframe embed / maps links
UC_Past ..> PES : links from site.data.past_events

note right of UC_Apply
Shown when site.application-page is set
and page.applications is true.
end note

note right of UC_Register
CTA in templates can link to site.registration-page.
registration/index.html links to forms.gle.
end note

note right of UC_Schedule
Rendered from site.data.program.program_rse25
via _includes/schedule.html.
end note
@enduml